vides academic services such as free tutoring, Living Learning Communities (LLCs) , and interaction with faculty outside of class.        LIVE CHEAPER    A four-year degree is cheaper than a five-year degree.  When you live on campus you are more likely to graduate on time.  We conveniently bill your account along with tuition and financial aid.  Your utilities and laundry are included, so no trips to the laundromat.        LIVE TOGETHER    Living on campus makes it easy to make friends!  Learn to step out of your comfort zone to meet new people and make life-long friends.  We support you – we have an amazing network of resources within the University and plenty of programming and leadership opportunities for you to make the most of your college experience.        LIVE FREELY    Experience living on your own and independently in one of the best cities in the world!  Come and go as you please… plan your day how you want without the need for a hefty commute time!        LIVE SAFE    Building security and live-in staff are around to respond to needs around the clock.  If you have concerns, there is always someone to speak with or refer you as necessary.        Why Live On Campus Ping                         UIC Logo        Campus Housing         Future    Apply    Housing Rates    Residence Halls    Services    Why Live on Campus      Current    Apply    Summer Housing    Housing During Breaks    Academic Support    Get Involved    Services      GUESTS AND CONFERENCES    Conference Housing    Guest Housing    Intern Housing    Medical Students        Button Menu    Dates to Know    Contact Us    Dock    MyContract    Student Affairs         Contact   818 S. Wolcott Ave., Suite 220, Chicago IL 60612  Phone: 312-355-6300  Fax: 312-355-6304  housing@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    Twitter    Instagram    YouTube             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calend